  "prompt": "How do you show appreciation to people that have helped you?",
  "response": "There are many ways to show appreciation to people who have helped you:\n\n1. Say \"thank you\" sincerely and specifically\n2. Write a heartfelt thank you note or card\n3. Give a small, thoughtful gift\n4. Offer to help them in return\n5. Verbally acknowledge their help to others\n6. Treat them to coffee or lunch\n7. Send a text or email expressing gratitude\n8. Give a recommendation or positive review\n9. Provide a recommendation letter\n10. Share how their help made a difference in your life\n11. Spend quality time with them\n12. Reciprocate their kindness when they need help\n13. Remember and celebrate their important events\n14. Listen and show genuine interest in their life\n15. Publicly recognize their contribution\n\nThe key is to be sincere, specific, and show that you truly value their support.",
